The paper proposes a method for improving the scalability and robustness of sparse subspace clustering, which is a machine learning technique used in computer vision and data analysis. The paper uses techniques from randomized clustering, multilayer graphs, and optimization to achieve these goals. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
